sition-vs-derived-from-height-moisture (the same elevation can be desert OR forest depending on the moisture sample at that pixel; deriving moisture from height collapses every low-elevation cell to one biome, eliminating coastal deserts and high-elevation forests as possibilities; same independent-data-composes-via-shared-spatial-grid pattern from chat-66 ping-pong-effects-dict + chat-67 UIElement-protocol = THIRD lesson reinforcing the independent-data-composes-via-shared-spatial-grid pattern in the graphics module). Catalog flipped 48+16 → 49+15 done+quiz_drafted in object-form `quiz_topics` shape (10th consecutive cohort applying the firmly-confirmed convention). **Graphics module advances 3/5 → 4/5 partial at chat-68 M1**; module-completeness stays 10/13 (graphics doesn't close in one chat; 1 graphics lesson remains: shaders). **Chat-64-startup archive-and-collapse M2-close discipline VALIDATED on FIFTH application:** wrote `support/archive/chat-68.md` joining `chat-64.md` + `chat-65.md` + `chat-66.md` + `chat-67.md` as the going-forward archival pattern (preserves heading + plan + Carry-forward disciplines + Phase-8 working file locations + Milestone narrative with M0 + M1 + M1+staging + M2 paragraphs); this section collapsed to stub at the same M2 close pointing to that archive. *See `support/archive/chat-68.md` for full chat-68 IN PROGRESS section content.*

