**Chat 67 closed end-to-end clean — no Finding-14 invocation needed.** M1 landed: graphics_ui_hud.html `done` with 'One Manager, Four Elements — Polymorphic Dispatch + Exponential Bar Smoothing + Proportional Minimap Projection in One Pygame Window' (~95-line pygame demo distilling the lesson's UIElement / HealthBar / Minimap / DialogBox / UIManager architecture into a single 2D pygame window: UIElement abstract base with no-op default update/render; HealthBar with `self.shown += (self.target - self.shown) * min(dt * 5, 1.0)` exponential approach; Minimap with `world_to_map(wx, wy) = (rect.x + int((wx / world_w) * rect.w), rect.y + int((wy / world_h) * rect.h))` proportional projection compressing a 1200×1200 world onto a 130×130 widget; DialogBox with chars-per-second typewriter + word-wrap; FloatNumber transient elements with rise + linear alpha fade and bool-return cull from chat-64 reuse; UIManager dispatching update/render polymorphically via `for e in self.elements.values(): e.update(dt) / e.render(surf)` with no isinstance branches anywhere; key 1 = damage 15, key 2 = heal 10, arrows move player at 220 px/s, D = trigger dialog) + 3 quiz Qs covering UIManager-polymorphic-dispatch-and-Open/Closed-Principle (UIManager iterates one collection through the UIElement protocol via Python's MRO, no isinstance checks, adding a UI type requires zero edits to UIManager) + exponential-smoothing-for-animated-bar-fill (`shown += (target - shown) * dt * 5` gives ease-out + no-overshoot + frame-rate-independence simultaneously vs alternatives; same exponential-approach formula as chat-46 platformer_camera + chat-44 physics_bounce_friction + chat-49 polish_tweening at different scopes) + minimap-proportional-projection-vs-camera-viewport-translation (camera viewport is TRANSLATION `screen_x = world_x - camera_x` showing a SLICE at 1:1 scale; minimap is PROPORTIONAL SCALING `map_x = rect.x + (world_x / world_w) * rect.w` of the WHOLE world; structurally different operations not parametric variations). Catalog flipped 47+17 → 48+16 done+quiz_drafted in object-form `quiz_topics` shape (9th consecutive cohort applying the firmly-confirmed convention). **Graphics module advances 2/5 → 3/5 partial at chat-67 M1**; module-completeness stays 10/13 (graphics doesn't close in one chat; 2 graphics lessons remain: procedural / shaders). **Chat-64-startup archive-and-collapse M2-close discipline VALIDATED on FOURTH application:** wrote `support/archive/chat-67.md` joining `chat-64.md` + `chat-65.md` + `chat-66.md` as the going-forward archival pattern (preserves heading + plan + Carry-forward disciplines + Phase-8 working file locations + Milestone narrative with M0 + M1 + M1+staging + M2 paragraphs); this section collapsed to stub at the same M2 close pointing to that archive. *See `support/archive/chat-67.md` for full chat-67 IN PROGRESS section content.*

