**Chat 33 closed clean across two attempts** — built and wired SVG #30 `rpg-stats-progression.svg` for `genres_rpg.html`. Chat-33-attempt-1 interrupted between milestone 3 (getBBox pre-clear, complete) and milestone 4 (lesson HTML edits + catalog finalize); chat-33-attempt-2 verified disk state (SVG on disk matches milestone-2 narrative, catalog at `built_unwired_chat_33`, lesson unwired) and resumed at milestone 4. **First time the chat-27 `built_unwired_chat_N` convention paid off as an interruption-recovery signal** — chat 31 was the first NORMAL exercise (clean within one chat); this is the first RECOVERY exercise. **Three-column character-sheet panel** at viewBox 720×440: STATS & VITALS (4-stat attributes STR/INT/DEX/VIT with indigo equipment bonuses, 3 semantic-colored vitals bars HP/MP/Stamina, amber XP bar Lvl 5→6, Warrior class), INVENTORY (4×4 representative slice of the 40-slot grid with 3 filled items, Carried legend, gold counter), EQUIPMENT (3 paper-doll slots — Weapon Iron Sword +5 ATK/+2 STR, Armor Leather +3 DEF/+1 VIT, Accessory empty). **Two new chat-33 findings:** (1) transform-text false positive in the getBBox walker — text inside `<g transform="...">` returns LOCAL coords, fix is to move text out; (2) cold-fetch timing context revises chat-32's rAF-removal magnitude — chat-33 with no rAF + active foreground tab measures ~315 ms cold-fetch; chat-32's 4.6 ms was likely hot-cache. rAF removal still the right convention. Phase 7 status delta: 13/15 wired-AND-render-checked unchanged; +1 wired-but-render-pending = chat-33 SVG; deferred drops 2/15 → 1/15 (`genres_tower_defense` only). Streaming-narrative discipline held across all 6 milestones — fourth consecutive clean exercise (chat 30 + 31 + 32 + 33 = 4/4 clean even counting the chat-33 mid-flight interruption, since recovery was clean). Detailed walkthrough lives in `status.md` → *Phase 7 progress (chat 33 — SVG #30 build: `rpg-stats-progression.svg` for `genres_rpg.html`)*.

